String is an object which represents sequence of char values

char[] ch={'S','t','r','i','n','g'};


same as

String s="String";


1> By String Literal
2> New Keyword


String s1="welcome"
String s2="welcome"
String s3="Java"




New Keyword


String s4 =new String("Welcome"); ---heap area one memory  

String  s5=new String("Welcome");  ---heap area another  memory 

Immutable : it will not change the original string until it is stored in a new variable

StringBuffer : Mutable
String : Immutable


StringBuilder  :NON-Synchronised (not thread safe)  : one function can accept mutiple threats simultaneously
StringBuffer   : SYNCHRONISED  (thread safe) : one function can accept one threat only

























